text: Béryl Laramé (born 1 July 1973) is a retired Seychellois female track and field athlete who specialised in high jump and triple jump events. She won two silvers and one bronze medal in the African Championships between 1993 and 2000. Her personal best in triple jump is 12.62 metres (achieved in 2000), which is still the Seychellois national record.
